<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="26">
Remarks. Poey (1858) described 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B0449A1C-9530-45E6-A45A-7C52AA882FD7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Lucifuga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Lucifuga subterraneus Poey 1858:96" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="subterraneus">Lucifuga subterraneus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Bythitidae" genus="Lucifuga" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dentata">Lucifuga dentata</taxonomicName>
after the generic description in the same volume, without type species designation. The designation of a type species was done subsequently by Jordan and Evermann (1896) as stated in Cohen and McCosker (1998) and Nielsen et al. (1999), and not by monotopy as stated in Eschmeyer (1998) and Nielsen (2003).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
